Location: rust/lichen-embassy/src/mock.rs:144-157

The static mut + unsafe block could be replaced with AtomicU64 using Relaxed ordering, eliminating the unsafe block entirely while having identical performance on x86/ARM:

```rust
use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU64, Ordering};
static SEED: AtomicU64 = AtomicU64::new(0xDEADBEEF);

fn fill_bytes(&mut self, buf: &mut [u8]) {
    for byte in buf.iter_mut() {
        let mut s = SEED.load(Ordering::Relaxed);
        s ^= s << 13;
        s ^= s >> 7;
        s ^= s << 17;
        SEED.store(s, Ordering::Relaxed);
        *byte = s as u8;
    }
}
```

This removes the SAFETY comment requirement entirely. The ponytail comment says 'simple xorshift instead of pulling in rand crate' - AtomicU64 is stdlib, no new dep.

Priority: P3 - Cleanup, not correctness. Current code works but sets a pattern of justifying unsafe when safe alternatives exist.
